<p><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">Damp squib</span><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p><strong><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">In the following question, out of the four alternatives, select the word opposite in meaning to the word given.</span></strong></p>

<p><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">Phlegmatic</span><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p>

<strong><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">&nbsp;In the following question, four words are given out of which one word is incorrectly spelt. Select the incorrectly spelt word.</span><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></strong>

<p><strong><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">In the following question, some part of the sentence may have errors. Find out which part of the sentence has an error and select the appropriate option. If a sentence is free from error, select &#39;No Error&#39;.</span></strong></p>

<p><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">The CEO only discussed (1)/ the new venture (2)/ with his manager. (3)/ No Error (4)</span><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p><strong><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">In the following question, out of the four alternatives, select the word similar in meaning to the word given.</span></strong></p>

<p><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">Jeopardy</span><span style="font-family:helvetica,helvetica_msfontservice,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p>

testSeriesIds.title: SSC CGL Mock Test Series 2026 (Tier I & Tier II)

instructions.value: The test contain 4 sections having 100 total questions.&nbsp;
Each question has 4 options out of which only one is correct.
You have to finish the test in 60 minutes.
<p>You will be awarded 2&nbsp;mark for each correct answer and 0.5&nbsp;marks will be deducted for each wrong&nbsp;answer.</p>
There is no negative marking for the questions that you have not attempted.
<p><span style="font-family: arial;">You can write this test only once.&nbsp;</span>Make sure that you complete the&nbsp;test before you submit the test and/or close the browser.</p>
